---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="For Organizers" description="Guide for tournament organizers - learn how to upload results, add your store, and grow your Digimon TCG community.">
  <Header />

  <main class="organizers-page">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="organizers-hero">
      <div class="hero-bg"></div>
      <div class="container hero-content">
        <div class="hero-text">
          <h1>For Organizers</h1>
          <p>Help grow your Digimon TCG community.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-mascot">
          <div class="digivice-glow">
            <img src="/brand/digivice.svg" alt="" class="digivice-icon" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="container organizers-layout">
      <!-- Sticky Sidebar -->
      <aside class="organizers-sidebar">
        <nav class="organizers-nav">
          <h3>Guide</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="#upload-results">Upload Results</a></li>
            <li><a href="#limitless">Limitless Integration</a></li>
            <li><a href="#community-links">Community Links</a></li>
            <li><a href="#add-store">Add Your Store</a></li>
            <li><a href="#request-scene">Request a Scene</a></li>
            <li><a href="#contributors">Become a Contributor</a></li>
            <li><a href="#report-error">Report an Error</a></li>
          </ul>
        </nav>
      </aside>

      <!-- Main Content -->
      <div class="organizers-content-area">

      <p class="intro-text">
        Tournament organizers and community builders are the backbone of the Digimon TCG scene. DigiLab helps you showcase your events, track your community's growth, and connect with players.
      </p>

      <!-- Upload Tournament Results -->
      <section class="content-category" id="upload-results">
        <h2><i class="bi bi-cloud-upload"></i> Upload Tournament Results</h2>

        <details class="content-item" open>
          <summary><i class="bi bi-list-check"></i> How to upload results</summary>
          <div class="content-body"><div class="content-body-inner">
            <p>Anyone can upload tournament results directly through the app. Our OCR system reads your Bandai TCG+ screenshots and extracts the data automatically.</p>
            <ol class="steps-list">
              <li>
                <strong><a href="https://app.digilab.cards/?tab=upload" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Go to the Upload Results tab</a></strong>
                <p>Open the Upload Results page from the sidebar in the app.</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Fill in tournament details</strong>
                <p>Select the store, date, event type, format, total players, and number of rounds.</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Upload your screenshots</strong>
                <p>Take screenshots of the final standings from the Bandai TCG+ app. Make sure placements, usernames, and member numbers are visible. You can upload multiple screenshots if standings span more than one screen.</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Review the extracted data</strong>
                <p>Our OCR system reads the screenshots and extracts player info automatically. Review the results, fix any OCR errors, and assign deck archetypes if known.</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Confirm and submit</strong>
                <p>Results go live immediately after submission. Ratings and statistics update automatically.</p>
              </li>
            </ol>
            <div class="cta-box">
              <a href="https://app.digilab.cards/?tab=upload" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                <i class="bi bi-cloud-upload"></i> Go to Upload Results
              </a>
            </div>
          </div></div>
        </details>

        <details class="content-item">
          <summary><i class="bi bi-info-circle"></i> What you'll need</summary>
          <div class="content-body"><div class="content-body-inner">
            <p><strong>Have ready before uploading:</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Screenshots of final standings from Bandai TCG+ (PNG, JPEG, or WebP)</li>
              <li>The store where the tournament was held</li>
              <li>Tournament date</li>
              <li>Total number of players and rounds</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Optional:</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Deck archetypes played (can be assigned during review or added later)</li>
              <li>Match history screenshots (for round-by-round records)</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="info-note">
              <i class="bi bi-info-circle"></i>
              Don't worry if you don't know every deck! Decks default to UNKNOWN and can be updated later by anyone in the community. You can also request new deck archetypes if one is missing from the dropdown.
            </div>
          </div></div>
        </details>
      </section>

      <!-- Limitless Integration -->
      <section class="content-category" id="limitless">
        <h2><i class="bi bi-cloud-arrow-down"></i> Limitless Integration</h2>

        <details class="content-item">
          <summary><i class="bi bi-arrow-repeat"></i> How Limitless sync works</summary>
          <div class="content-body"><div class="content-body-inner">
            <p>Online tournaments from Limitless TCG are synced automatically into DigiLab. Results, placements, and deck archetypes are imported weekly. Online tournaments appear in the "Online" scene and feed the same rating system as in-person events.</p>
          </div></div>
        </details>

        <details class="content-item">
          <summary><i class="bi bi-people"></i> Currently synced organizers</summary>
          <div class="content-body"><div class="content-body-inner">
            <p>The following Tier 1 organizers are currently synced:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Eagle's Nest</strong></li>
              <li><strong>PHOENIX REBORN</strong></li>
              <li><strong>DMV Drakes</strong></li>
              <li><strong>MasterRukasu</strong></li>
            </ul>
            <p>These organizers run regular online events that are automatically imported.</p>
          </div></div>
        </details>

        <details class="content-item">
          <summary><i class="bi bi-plus-circle"></i> Get your organizer page added</summary>
          <div class="content-body"><div class="content-body-inner">
            <p>If you run online tournaments on Limitless TCG, contact us to add your organizer page to the sync.</p>
            <p><strong>Provide:</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Your Limitless organizer name and page URL</li>
              <li>Approximate event frequency</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="cta-box">
              <a href="https://discord.gg/digilab" class="btn btn-outline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                <i class="bi bi-discord"></i> Ask on Discord
              </a>
            </div>
          </div></div>
        </details>
      </section>

      <!-- Community Links -->
      <section class="content-category" id="community-links">
        <h2><i class="bi bi-link-45deg"></i> Community Links</h2>

        <details class="content-item">
          <summary><i class="bi bi-link"></i> What are community links?</summary>
          <div class="content-body"><div class="content-body-inner">
            <p>Every store and organizer on DigiLab has a unique community link. When shared, it filters the entire app to show only that community's data — tournaments, players, meta, everything.</p>
            <p>URL format: <code>app.digilab.cards/?community=your-store-slug</code></p>
          </div></div>
        </details>

        <details class="content-item">
          <summary><i class="bi bi-search"></i> How to find your community link</summary>
          <div class="content-body"><div class="content-body-inner">
            <p>To get your store's community link:</p>
            <ol class="steps-list">
              <li>Go to the <a href="https://app.digilab.cards/?tab=stores" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Stores</strong> tab</a></li>
              <li>Find your store and click it to open the modal</li>
              <li>Look for the <strong>"Share Community View"</strong> button in the modal</li>
              <li>Copy the link and share it!</li>
            </ol>
          </div></div>
        </details>

        <details class="content-item">
          <summary><i class="bi bi-lightbulb"></i> Use cases</summary>
          <div class="content-body"><div class="content-body-inner">
            <p><strong>Discord server:</strong> Post the link so players can check standings anytime.</p>
            <p><strong>Social media:</strong> Share after events so players can see updated results.</p>
            <p><strong>Store website:</strong> Link to your community's DigiLab page for tournament info.</p>
          </div></div>
        </details>
      </section>

      <!-- Add Your Store -->
      <section class="content-category" id="add-store">
        <h2><i class="bi bi-shop-window"></i> Add Your Store</h2>

        <details class="content-item">
          <summary><i class="bi bi-shop"></i> Physical stores</summary>
          <div class="content-body"><div class="content-body-inner">
            <p>We want to include every store that runs Digimon TCG events! There are two ways to request a new store:</p>
            <p><strong>Option 1: Through the app</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Go to the <a href="https://app.digilab.cards/?tab=stores" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Stores</strong> tab</a></li>
              <li>Click the <strong>"Request Store"</strong> button</li>
              <li>Fill in store name, city/state, and your scene</li>
              <li>Submit — your request goes directly to your scene admin for review</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Option 2: Ask on Discord</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Join our Discord and share the store details in the appropriate channel</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="cta-box cta-box--dual">
              <a href="https://app.digilab.cards/?tab=stores" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                <i class="bi bi-shop"></i> Request Store in App
              </a>
              <a href="https://discord.gg/digilab" class="btn btn-outline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                <i class="bi bi-discord"></i> Ask on Discord
              </a>
            </div>
          </div></div>
        </details>

        <details class="content-item">
          <summary><i class="bi bi-camera-video"></i> Online organizers</summary>
          <div class="content-body"><div class="content-body-inner">
            <p>Already running webcam events? Online organizers are supported on DigiLab! To get listed:</p>
            <p><strong>Provide:</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Platform name (e.g., your Discord server or community name)</li>
              <li>Limitless organizer page URL</li>
              <li>Discord server invite link</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Events sync automatically via Limitless integration once your organizer page is added.</p>
            <div class="cta-box">
              <a href="https://discord.gg/digilab" class="btn btn-outline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                <i class="bi bi-discord"></i> Ask on Discord
              </a>
            </div>
          </div></div>
        </details>

        <details class="content-item">
          <summary><i class="bi bi-check-circle"></i> Store requirements</summary>
          <div class="content-body"><div class="content-body-inner">
            <p><strong>Physical stores</strong> should meet the following:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Run regular Digimon TCG events (at least monthly)</li>
              <li>Use Bandai TCG+ or Limitless for tournament management</li>
              <li>Be open to the public (not private play groups)</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Online organizers</strong> should meet the following:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Run regular scheduled events</li>
              <li>Have public registration open to all players</li>
            </ul>
          </div></div>
        </details>
      </section>

      <!-- Request a New Scene -->
      <section class="content-category" id="request-scene">
        <h2><i class="bi bi-globe"></i> Request a New Scene</h2>

        <details class="content-item">
          <summary><i class="bi bi-geo-alt"></i> How to get your scene added</summary>
          <div class="content-body"><div class="content-body-inner">
            <p>Want to bring DigiLab to your community? First, make sure you meet the prerequisites:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Your area has at least 2-3 active stores or organizers running regular Digimon events</li>
              <li>You have a community contact who can help gather initial tournament data</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Then submit your request:</p>
            <p><strong>Option 1: Through the app</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Go to the <a href="https://app.digilab.cards/?tab=stores" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Stores</strong> tab</a></li>
              <li>Click the <strong>"Request Scene"</strong> button</li>
              <li>Provide details about your community and stores</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Option 2: Ask on Discord</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Join our Discord and share your scene request with community details</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="cta-box cta-box--dual">
              <a href="https://app.digilab.cards/?tab=stores" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                <i class="bi bi-globe"></i> Request Scene in App
              </a>
              <a href="https://discord.gg/digilab" class="btn btn-outline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                <i class="bi bi-discord"></i> Ask on Discord
              </a>
            </div>
          </div></div>
        </details>

        <details class="content-item">
          <summary><i class="bi bi-map"></i> What makes a scene?</summary>
          <div class="content-body"><div class="content-body-inner">
            <p>A "scene" in DigiLab is a community of players who regularly compete against each other. This is usually defined by:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Geography</strong> — A metro area, state, or collection of nearby cities</li>
              <li><strong>Community</strong> — Players who know each other and attend the same events</li>
              <li><strong>Activity</strong> — At least 2-3 stores or organizers with regular events</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Examples: a metro area like "Houston TCG", a state-level scene like "Florida Digimon", or a regional community like "Southeast Tamers"</p>
          </div></div>
        </details>
      </section>

      <!-- Become a Contributor -->
      <section class="content-category" id="contributors">
        <h2><i class="bi bi-person-badge"></i> Become a Contributor</h2>

        <details class="content-item">
          <summary><i class="bi bi-star"></i> What is a contributor?</summary>
          <div class="content-body"><div class="content-body-inner">
            <p>Most users won't need contributor access — anyone can upload tournament results via screenshots. Contributors are trusted community members with additional admin capabilities.</p>
            <p><strong>Admin contributors</strong> can:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Enter tournament results manually (without screenshots)</li>
              <li>Edit existing tournaments and results</li>
              <li>Manage player records and deck archetypes</li>
              <li>Approve or reject deck archetype requests from the community</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Super Admin contributors</strong> additionally manage stores and format settings.</p>
          </div></div>
        </details>

        <details class="content-item">
          <summary><i class="bi bi-person-plus"></i> How do I become a contributor?</summary>
          <div class="content-body"><div class="content-body-inner">
            <p>We're looking for active tournament organizers and community members who regularly attend events. To become a contributor:</p>
            <ol class="steps-list">
              <li>
                <strong>Build a track record</strong>
                <p>Upload a few tournaments via the <a href="https://app.digilab.cards/?tab=upload" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Upload Results</a> page so we can verify data quality.</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Express interest</strong>
                <p>Let us know you'd like contributor access when uploading results.</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Get set up</strong>
                <p>We'll provide you with admin credentials and a quick orientation on the admin tools.</p>
              </li>
            </ol>
            <div class="cta-box">
              <a href="https://discord.gg/digilab" class="btn btn-outline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                <i class="bi bi-discord"></i> Ask on Discord
              </a>
            </div>
          </div></div>
        </details>
      </section>

      <!-- Report an Error -->
      <section class="content-category" id="report-error">
        <h2><i class="bi bi-exclamation-triangle"></i> Report an Error</h2>

        <details class="content-item">
          <summary><i class="bi bi-flag"></i> How to report data errors</summary>
          <div class="content-body"><div class="content-body-inner">
            <p>Spotted something wrong with a tournament result, player record, or deck assignment? There are two ways to report it:</p>
            <p><strong>Option 1: Through the app</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Open the player, tournament, or deck modal in the <a href="https://app.digilab.cards" target="_blank" rel="noopener">app</a></li>
              <li>Click the <strong>"Report Error"</strong> button in the modal footer</li>
              <li>Describe what's wrong and submit</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Option 2: Ask on Discord</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Join our Discord and describe the error in the appropriate channel</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="info-note">
              <i class="bi bi-info-circle"></i>
              All reports are routed to your scene's coordination channel on Discord for fast resolution.
            </div>
            <div class="cta-box cta-box--dual">
              <a href="https://app.digilab.cards" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                <i class="bi bi-flag"></i> Report in App
              </a>
              <a href="https://discord.gg/digilab" class="btn btn-outline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                <i class="bi bi-discord"></i> Ask on Discord
              </a>
            </div>
          </div></div>
        </details>

        <details class="content-item">
          <summary><i class="bi bi-bug"></i> How to report a bug</summary>
          <div class="content-body"><div class="content-body-inner">
            <p>Found a bug or something not working right? Let us know:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>What you were trying to do</li>
              <li>What you expected to happen</li>
              <li>What actually happened</li>
              <li>Screenshots if possible</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="cta-box">
              <a href="https://discord.gg/digilab" class="btn btn-outline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                <i class="bi bi-bug"></i> Report a Bug on Discord
              </a>
            </div>
          </div></div>
        </details>
      </section>

      </div><!-- end organizers-content-area -->

      <!-- Contact CTA -->
      <section class="contact-cta">
        <h2><i class="bi bi-chat-square-text"></i> Questions?</h2>
        <p>If you have questions about submitting results or getting involved, don't hesitate to reach out.</p>
        <div class="cta-buttons">
          <a href="https://discord.gg/digilab" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            <i class="bi bi-discord"></i> Discord
          </a>
          <a href="https://github.com/lopezmichael/digilab-app" class="btn btn-outline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            <i class="bi bi-github"></i> GitHub
          </a>
          <a href="https://ko-fi.com/digilab" class="btn btn-outline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            <i class="bi bi-cup-hot"></i> Ko-fi
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  // Highlight active section in sidebar based on scroll position
  const sections = document.querySelectorAll('.content-category[id]');
  const navLinks = document.querySelectorAll('.organizers-nav a');

  function updateActiveLink() {
    const scrollPos = window.scrollY + 120;

    sections.forEach((section) => {
      const sectionTop = section.offsetTop;
      const sectionHeight = section.offsetHeight;
      const sectionId = section.getAttribute('id');

      if (scrollPos >= sectionTop && scrollPos < sectionTop + sectionHeight) {
        navLinks.forEach((link) => {
          link.classList.remove('active');
          if (link.getAttribute('href') === `#${sectionId}`) {
            link.classList.add('active');
          }
        });
      }
    });
  }

  let ticking = false;
  window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
    if (!ticking) {
      window.requestAnimationFrame(() => {
        updateActiveLink();
        ticking = false;
      });
      ticking = true;
    }
  });

  updateActiveLink();

  navLinks.forEach((link) => {
    link.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
      e.preventDefault();
      const targetId = link.getAttribute('href')?.slice(1);
      const targetSection = document.getElementById(targetId || '');
      if (targetSection) {
        const offsetTop = targetSection.offsetTop - 80;
        window.scrollTo({
          top: offsetTop,
          behavior: 'smooth'
        });
      }
    });
  });
</script>

<style>
  /* ===== Hero Section ===== */
  .organizers-hero {
    position: relative;
    padding: var(--space-12) 0 var(--space-16);
  }

  .hero-bg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary-dark, #061a2e) 0%, var(--color-primary) 100%);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
    z-index: -2;
  }

  .hero-content {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .hero-text h1 {
    color: #ffffff;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .hero-text p {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .hero-mascot {
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .digivice-glow {
    position: relative;
    width: 72px;
    height: 72px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .digivice-glow::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: -8px;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(0, 200, 255, 0.4) 0%, rgba(0, 200, 255, 0) 70%);
    border-radius: 50%;
    animation: digivice-pulse 3s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  .digivice-icon {
    width: 56px;
    height: 56px;
    filter: brightness(0) invert(1);
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  @keyframes digivice-pulse {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 0.6; transform: scale(1); }
    50% { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1.1); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero-content {
      flex-direction: column;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .hero-mascot {
      order: -1;
    }
  }

  /* ===== Layout ===== */
  .organizers-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-8);
    max-width: 1000px;
    padding-top: var(--space-8);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-12);
    align-items: start;
  }

  /* ===== Sidebar ===== */
  .organizers-sidebar {
    position: sticky;
    top: calc(57px + var(--space-6));
  }

  .organizers-nav h3 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-xs);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .organizers-nav ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .organizers-nav li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
  }

  .organizers-nav a {
    display: block;
    padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    border-left: 2px solid transparent;
    transition: all var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .organizers-nav a:hover {
    color: var(--color-text);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-left-color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .organizers-nav a.active {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    background: rgba(10, 48, 85, 0.08);
    border-left-color: var(--color-primary);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
  }

  /* ===== Main Content Area ===== */
  .organizers-content-area {
    min-width: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .organizers-layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .organizers-sidebar {
      position: relative;
      top: 0;
    }

    .organizers-nav ul {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: var(--space-2);
    }

    .organizers-nav li {
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    .organizers-nav a {
      padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3);
      background: var(--color-surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-left: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: var(--radius-full);
      white-space: nowrap;
      font-size: var(--font-size-xs);
    }

    .organizers-nav a:hover,
    .organizers-nav a.active {
      border-left: 1px solid var(--color-primary);
